OL,3,C#50,000 approved for study to explore
OL,4,Cfuture of 'eyesore' factory
OL,6,FSaid to be the first ferro-concrete
OL,7,Fcar factory built in Britain, the site
OL,8,Fhas had a number of guises over its
OL,9,Flong history, including being used for
OL,10,Fthe manufacture of planes and aircraft
OL,11,Fengines during the Second World War,
OL,12,Fand later the manufacture of
OL,13,Fwellington boots, before its final use
OL,14,Fas an underlay factory.
OL,16,FIts 'Category B' listing means that
OL,17,Fthe property is considered to be one
OL,18,Fof "special architectural or historic
OL,19,Finterest" and a "major examples of a
OL,20,Fparticular period, style or building
OL,21,Ftype".
